#virtual environment in python#

step1: create a directory and go inside the directory

step2: create a virtual environment
command:       python -m venv myenv

step3: to activate the virtual environment in windows:
command:       myenv\Scripts\activate.bat 

       to activate the virtual environment in mac or linux:    
command:       source myenv/bin/activate

step4: to close the created venv
command:        deactivate

step5: to know which packages are installed in the venv
command:        pip freeze

step6: save all the packages versions in one file named: requirements.txt
command:        pip freeze > requirements.txt

step7: to install the listed packages in the requirements.txt file
command:     pip install -r requirements.txt

            
